# ansible-lint config for the infra/ansible deployment playbook.
#
# `var-naming[no-role-prefix]` requires every role-scoped variable to carry
# its role name as a prefix. That rule exists to stop *independently
# reusable / Galaxy-published* roles from silently clobbering each other's
# unprefixed vars. infra/ansible is the opposite case: ONE cohesive,
# single-run converge (site.yml) whose roles are deliberately coupled and
# intentionally share variables across role boundaries via `default()`
# (e.g. `secrets_env_file`, the `app_*` deploy paths, the `dh_*` Django
# settings are produced by one role and consumed by several others).
# Force-prefixing every var would break those intentional cross-role
# references for zero real collision-safety gain here. Skipping only this
# one sub-rule is the correct scope; every other ansible-lint rule (incl.
# syntax-check, fqcn, risky-file-permissions, etc.) stays fully enforced.
skip_list:
  - var-naming[no-role-prefix]
